Scoring the Top 40 hit Girl Talk and earned two Grammy Awards nominations, it featured unreleased vocals from Left Eye.

Tionne and Rozonda seem intent on re-establishing their brand once more and on the back of this film look set to be re-signing with LA Reid, the guy who made them go bankrupt to begin with.

The legendary girl group will played The Mixtape Festival at Hersheypark Stadium, in Hershey, Pennsylvania, from July 26-27, alongside New Kids On The Block, Hanson and Boyz II Men.

Directed by Charles Stone III and written by Kate Lanier the upcoming biographical film will air on VH1 this month.

